  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The model is intended to predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5 operating at 2500 RPM with 5 L/min nominal flow. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification covers inlet velocity, fluid viscosity, and power-law hemolysis exponents. All 13 credibility factors have been evaluated; 7 factors are fully assessed and 6 carry epistemic gap flags consistent with MRL 5. The assessment team concludes that the achieved credibility levels are sufficient for the intended regulatory submission context and the package is accepted at Low assurance level.",
