      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to Navier-Stokes and power-law hemolysis transport equations with demonstrated second-order convergence.",
      "rationale": "MMS applied to Navier-Stokes solver; hemolysis transport equation verified via simplified analytical benchmark only. Full MMS for coupled system not completed, leaving one gradation gap."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 2 % on all primary QoI using three systematically refined meshes with refinement ratio ≥ 1.3.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh GCI study performed; GCI on hemolysis index is 3.2 %, marginally exceeding the 2 % threshold. Velocity field GCI meets criteria. Overall achieved level assessed as 3."
    },
